pürt und neu kontextualisiert.  aIn »heavy floating«, the author develops a figure of thought that traces and re-contextualizes floating people in European dance and cultural history.  afunded by VG-Wort  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aChoreographyzGermanyxHistory. 4aFilm. 4aGravitas. 4aLeichtigkeit. 4aLiteratur. 4aModerner Tanz. 4aModernes Ballett. 4aPhysik. 4aPina Bausch. 4aRelativitätstheorie. 4aSchweben. 4aSchwerelosigkeit. 4aSchwerkraft. 4aTanz. 4aTanzforschung. 4aTanzgeschichte. 4aTanzwissenschaft. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Dance / General.2bisacsh  aDance History.  aDance Research.  aDance Studies.  aDance.  aEase.  aFilm.  aGravitas.  aGravity.  aHovering.  aLiterature.  aModern Ballett.  aModern Dance.  aPhysics.  aPina Bausch.  aTheory of Relativity.  aWeightlessness.2 aVG-Wortefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2019z9783110605785oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.14361/9783839446652zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839446652423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783839446652.jpg  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPKb2019